SIMPLE: cascade
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cascade
<hw>Cas*cade"</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧s*k⟦amac⟧d")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cascade</ets>, fr. It. <ets>cascata</ets>, fr. <ets>cascare</ets>
to fall.]</ety> <def>A fall of water over a precipice, as in a river or
brook; a waterfall less than a cataract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The silver brook . . . pours the white <qex>cascade</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longjellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now murm'ring soft, now roaring in <qex>cascade</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cascade</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cascade
<hw>Cas*cade"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To fall in a
cascade.</def> <rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To vomit.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>
<rj><au>Smollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cascade method</ent>⟦br⟧
